Claims CLAIMS : 1. An apparatus (30) for determining well integrity of a hydrocarbon-producing well (10), the apparatus (30) comprising: an acoustic frequency generator (32) for generating a plurality of acoustic frequencies; a modulator (36) for selecting a set of acoustic frequencies from the plurality of acoustic frequencies, and for applying a transmission sequence; a transceiver (40) for transmitting the set of acoustic frequencies in the transmission sequence into a well bore of the hydrocarbon-producing well (10), at a predetermined depth of the hydrocarbon-producing well (10), and for receiving reflected resonances with respect to a sub-set of acoustic frequencies from the set of acoustic frequencies, from one or more well integrity layers (44-54) in a field of view (56) of the set of acoustic frequencies; and a processor (60) for determining one or more well integrity features based on the reflected resonances. 2. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 wherein the processor comprises filtering the reflected resonances to obtain resonances for the one or more well integrity layers (44-54). 3. The apparatus (30) of claim 2 further comprising determining resonant peaks from the resonances for each well integrity layer (44-54). 4. The apparatus (30) of claim 3 wherein a distance between subsequent resonant peaks for each well integrity layer (44-54) is used to determine a thickness for each of each well integrity layer (44-54). 5. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 further comprising determining a geometry characterization image (136) for one or more well integrity layers (44-54) based on the reflected resonances. 6. The apparatus (30) of claim 5 wherein the processor (60) further comprises a resonance model (64), wherein the resonance model (64) is used to apply a 

 correction factor to at least one of the one or more well integrity features or the geometry characterization image (136). 7. The apparatus (30) of claim 6 wherein the correction factor applies a correction for an impact of at least one of temperature, pressure, material oxidation, well operating parameters, on the reflected resonances. 8. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 wherein the set of acoustic frequencies are transmitted one at a time using a chirp signal. 9. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 wherein the set of acoustic frequencies are transmitted simultaneously. 10. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 wherein the set of acoustic frequencies are transmitted as a coded signal. 11. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 wherein the one or more well integrity features comprise at least one of a thickness of each of the one or more well integrity layers; a presence of a micro-annulus, and a thickness of the micro-annulus, detection of medium in the micro-annulus, presence of cement de-bonding, or extent of cement de-bonding. 12. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 wherein the acoustic frequency generator (32) generates a bulk wave with frequencies in a range of about 1-10 Mega Hertz. 13. The apparatus (30) of claim 5 wherein the geometry characterization image (136) is a three - dimensional image. 14. The apparatus (30) of claim 1 wherein the one or more well integrity layers (44-54) comprise casing wall (44), casing-cement interface (46), cement wall (50), cement- bedrock interface (52), and a bedrock (54). 15. A method (200) for determining well integrity of a hydrocarbon-producing well (10), the method comprising: generating (212) a plurality of acoustic frequencies; 

 modulating (214) a set of acoustic frequencies from the plurality of acoustic frequencies, and applying a transmission sequence for the set of acoustic frequencies; transmitting (216) the set of acoustic frequencies through a well bore at a predetermined depth of the hydrocarbon-producing well (10); receiving (218) reflected resonances with respect to a sub-set of acoustic frequencies from the set of acoustic frequencies, from one or more well integrity layers (44-54) in a field of view of the set of the acoustic frequencies; and processing (220) the reflected resonances to determine one or more well integrity features. 16. The method (200) of claim 15 wherein processing comprises filtering the reflected resonances to obtain resonances for the one or more well integrity layers (44-54). 17. The method (200) of claim 16 wherein processing (220) comprises determining resonant peaks from the resonances for each well integrity layer. 18. The method (200) of claim 17 wherein a distance between subsequent resonant peaks for each well integrity layer (44-54) is used while processing to determine a thickness for each of each well integrity layer (44-54). 19. The method (200) of claim 15 further comprising determining a geometry characterization image (136) for one or more well integrity layers (44-54) based on the reflected resonances. 20. The method (200) of claim 19 wherein processing (220) further comprises using a resonance model (64) to apply a correction factor to at least one of the one or more well integrity features or the geometry characterization image
